17// Register : ACCESSCTRL_LOCK
18// Description : Once a LOCK bit is written to 1, ACCESSCTRL silently ignores
19// writes from that master. LOCK is writable only by a Secure,
20// Privileged processor or debugger.
21//
22// LOCK bits are only writable when their value is zero. Once set,
23// they can never be cleared, except by a full reset of ACCESSCTRL
24//
25// Setting the LOCK bit does not affect whether an access raises a
